<TITLE> Parliament breaks for 15 days </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 13 (bdnews24.com)Speaker Abdul Hamid adjourned current session of parliament on Tuesday for 15 days. He said the session would resume on October 28. Parliament's business advisory committee had earlier decided to allow a recess and extension of the third session. Chief whip Abdus Shahid told bdnews24.com that the house was adjourned to avoid having to hold another session in December. According to the constitution, parliament must sit again within 60 days of the last day of a session. Shahid said the House may run up to the first week of November though the business advisory committee headed by the speaker was yet to decide on the exact tenure of the current session. The third session started on Sept 7 and was adjourned once already for Eid and Durga Puja festivals. bdnew
